--- PART 3: P_m(t) = t^m * b(m, -1/t) ---
P_m(t) = sum_{j=0}^m (-1)^j C(m+j,2j) t^{m-j}
       = t^m * sum_{j=0}^m C(m+j,2j) * (-1/t)^j
       = t^m * b(m, -1/t)
  m=3, k=1: Q_k^m * b(m,-1/Q_k) = 6.597547e-14
  m=3, k=2: Q_k^m * b(m,-1/Q_k) = 8.302550e-16
